    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 9th level in warlock, if the wearer of your talisman is a creature other than you, they can cast any warlock spell you know through the talisman. The spell is of the same level as your pact spell slot, and uses your spell save DC, spell attack bonus, and spellcasting ability as if you are the caster, but is otherwise treated as if they cast the spell. Casting a spell in this way does not use your Pact Spell Slot. You may use this feature once per long rest.</p>",
